Steps to Set Up Firebase:

1. Go to the Firebase Console: Open Firebase Console, and sign in with your Google account.

2. Create a New Project: Follow the instructions to create a new Firebase project.

3. Add Firebase to Your Web App:

Click on the Web icon (</>) to register your app.
Follow the setup instructions provided by Firebase to add Firebase SDK to your web application.
Enable Realtime Database:

4. In the Firebase console, navigate to "Realtime Database" and create a database.
Set up the database rules for public read and write access (for testing purposes; you should restrict this later based on your requirements).
json

Copy code below to "rules" (change false to true)
==========================
{
  "rules": {
    ".read": true,
    ".write": true
  }
}
==========================

5. JavaScript File: comments.js
This script will handle connecting to Firebase, submitting comments, and displaying them on your page.

5.1. Example:
/assets/js/your-voice.js

javascript

**Copy code** (Config Firebase), generated by Firebase.

// Your web app's Firebase configuration (replace with your actual config details)
var firebaseConfig = {
    apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY", 
    authDomain: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID.firebaseapp.com", 
    databaseURL: "https://YOUR_DATABASE_NAME.firebaseio.com",
    projectId: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
    storageBucket: "YOUR_BUCKET.appspot.com",
    messagingSenderId: "YOUR_SENDER_ID",
    appId: "YOUR_APP_ID"
};

** Initialize**
// Initialize Firebase
firebase.initializeApp(firebaseConfig);

** Like import packages from python**
// Reference to your database service
